 e^x = \sum_{i=0}^{\infty} \frac{x^n}{n!} 
\begin{align} \frac{d}{dx}e^x &= \frac{d}{dx}\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} \frac{x^n}{n!} \\ &= \sum_{i=0}^{\infty} \frac{d}{dx}\frac{x^n}{n!} \\ &= \sum_{i=1}^{\infty}\frac{x^{n-1}}{(n-1)!} \end{align} 
 \frac{d}{dx} x^n = nx^{n-1}. 
 \frac{d}{dx} x^2 = 2x \quad\quad\frac{d}{dx} x^3 = 3x^2. 
\frac{d}{dx}\frac{x^n}{n!} =\frac{1}{n!} \frac{d}{dx} x^n = \frac{1}{n!}nx^{n-1} = \frac{n}{n\cdot(n-1)!}x^{n-1} = \frac{x^{n-1}}{(n-1)!}. 
